Machimia homopolia is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Turner in 1946. It is found in Australia, where it has been recorded from New South Wales.The wingspan is 22â€“25 mm. The forewings are pale brownish-grey, the costa edged with whitish. The stigmata is minute and fuscous. The first discal spot is found at one-fourth, the plical spot is beyond it and the second discal spot is found at three-fifths. The hindwings are greyish.